dc_title_s: Right of Way Street Centerlines: San Mateo County, California, 2006
dc_description_s: This polyline shapefile depicts the public space Right of Way (ROW) centerlines for street segments managed by the County of San Mateo. When property is developed, property owners dedicate part of the land as public ROW for streets, sidewalks, utilities and similar public uses. Similarly, activities occuring in public ROW areas may require securing a permit. This layer is part of a collection of GIS data for San Mateo County, California.This coverage can be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analyses of geospatial data.
